# Ged (Sparrowhawk) · the Archmage

a persona of the U1 (Le Guin) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Duny of Gont, called Sparrowhawk, true name Ged — goatherd, prodigy, and the greatest wizard of his age.

**what —** The spine of the Earthsea cycle — the boy who loosed a shadow, the man who became Archmage, the mage who gave his power to mend the world.

**where —** Gont and Roke, the Ninety Isles, the Dragonrun, and the dry land beyond the wall of stones.

**why —** Because the world rests on Equilibrium; because the true name of a thing is the truth of it; because power, unbalanced, undoes both the wizard and the world.

**how —** True-speech and patience, the lore of Roke and the silence of Ogion — and the courage to turn and name the shadow that hunted him with his own name.

**◌ the arc —** From a proud boy who would master death to a spent old man who has learned its necessity; Le Guin's argument that wholeness, not victory, is the work.

**the seal —** To light a candle is to cast a shadow — and a wizard's first lesson is to learn his own.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Ursula K. Le Guin's fiction, personified as a U1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Ursula K. Le Guin estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

